    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT279-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">vaṟpuṟukkun tōḻikkuk kiḻatti uraittatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by HER to the confidante who encourages [her]. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT279">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> tirimarup perumai yiruṇiṟa maiyāṉ</l>
          <l> varumiṭa ṟiyātta pakuvāyt teṇmaṇi</l>
          <l> pulampukoḷ yāmat tiyaṅkuto ṟicaikku</l>
          <l> mitupoḻu tākavum vārār kollō</l>
          <l> maḻaikeḻu maṟanta māyirun tuṟukaṟ</l>
          <l> ṟukaḷcūḻ yāṉaiyiṟ poliyat tōṉṟu</l>
          <l> mirumpal kuṉṟam pōkit</l>
          <l> tiruntiṟaip paṇaitō ḷuḷḷā tōrē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>When with every motion, at midnight filled with loneliness <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> pulampu koḷ yāmattu </term>: cf. note on KT 207.3. Cām.'s gloss <term xml:lang="ta"> vaḷarkiṉṟa </term> "long" is probably just a conjecture.</note> ,</l>
          <l rend="indent">the slit-mouthed clear bell sounds, tied to the prominent <note place="foot"> Is this the meaning of <term xml:lang="ta"> varu miṭaṟu </term>?</note> neck</l>
          <l rend="indent2">of the night-coloured buffalo, the buffalo <note place="foot"> Do <term xml:lang="ta"> erumai </term> and <term xml:lang="ta"> maiyāṉ </term> refer to the same animal? T.V.G. takes the latter to be the cow of the former, which would again give a nice male-female pair. Actually the ending - <term xml:lang="ta">āṉ </term> would suggest another male animal, but since in the case of ā/āṉ "cow" both terms can refer to the female animal, the same might be conceivable for <term xml:lang="ta"> maiyāṉ </term>.</note> with twisted horns</l>
          <l>– even as this time is arising, doesn't he come,</l>
          <l>who doesn't remember the bamboo shoulder with perfect joints</l>
          <l>[and] has gone [across] many dark hills</l>
          <l rend="indent">where the big, dark, thick stones, that were forgotten</l>
          <l rend="indent9">as the rain came up,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">seem to glitter like elephants covered in dust?</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
